"Southwold, Suffolk, England":"Southwold, Suffolk, England"},"nl":{"Abt 1435–Abt 1488":"circa 1435–circa 1488","1435–1488":"1435–1488","1431–1487":"1431–1487","1461–1513":"1461–1513","1416–1486":"1416–1486","1513":"1513","1435":"1435","1455":"1455","1488":"1488","1487":"1487","1486":"1486","1431":"1431","Abt 1435":"circa 1435","1461":"1461","Abt 1488":"circa 1488","18 July 1487":"18 juli 1487","1416":"1416","Blythburgh Manor,Southwold,Suffolkshire,England":"Southwold, Suffolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Blythburgh, Suffolk, England":"Blythburgh, Suffolk, England","Southwold, Suffolk, England":"Southwold, Suffolk, England"},"en":{"Abt 1435–Abt 1488":"about 1435–about 1488","1435–1488":"1435–1488","1431–1487":"1431–1487","1461–1513":"1461–1513","1416–1486":"1416–1486","1513":"1513","1435":"1435","1455":"1455","1488":"1488","1487":"1487","1486":"1486","1431":"1431","Abt 1435":"about 1435","1461":"1461","Abt 1488":"about 1488","18 July 1487":"18 July 1487","1416":"1416","Blythburgh Manor,Southwold,Suffolkshire,England":"Southwold, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Blythburgh, Suffolk, England":"Blythburgh, Suffolk, England","Southwold, Suffolk, England":"Southwold, Suffolk, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hoo","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese: Chi, Wai Lam, Wing, Beng, Chin, Gan, Hing, Hui, Kee, Lai, Lai Ching, Mei-Mei.","Chinese:","variant Romanization of the surname   Hu  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Hu","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Wei, Jian, Ming, Ping, Bin, Yi, Ying, Jing, Xiao, Qi, Yan, Chi.  Korean Chang, Chung, Min, Yiping, Chong, Chul, Hu, Jung Soo, Sang Hoon, Tian, Wook, Yiming.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 胡, a term referring to the ethnic minorities in ancient northern and western China: (i) from Hu (胡), the name of an ancient state (located in present-day Henan province) during the Western Zhou dynasty (1046–771  BC ). After it was annexed by the state of Zheng (located in present-day Shaanxi and Henan provinces) in the 26th year of the reign of King Ping of Zhou (died 720  BC ), people from the fief adopted 胡, the name of the state, as their surname. (ii) from Hu (胡), the name of a state (located in present-day Anhui province). After it was annexed by the state of Chu in the 15th year of the reign of Duke Ding of Lu (ruler of the state of Lu, reigned 509–495  BC ), people from the fief adopted 胡, the name of the state, as their surname. (iii) from the personal name of Hu Gong Man (胡公满, Duke Hu of Chen), the posthumous title of Yu Man. He was given the fief of Chen (located mainly in present-day Henan and Anhui province) by King Wu of Zhou (<i>c.</i> 1087–1043  BC ). (iv) from the personal name of Hu Guang (胡廣), who changed his original surname 黃 to 胡 during the Eastern Han dynasty (25–220  AD ). (v) from the Hu Gu (胡骨) or He Gu (纥骨) families from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China, who changed their surname to 胡 during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ).","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 扈, meaning ‘retinue’ in ancient Chinese: (i) from Hu (扈), the name of an ancient state (located in present-day Shaanxi province) dating back to the Xia dynasty (2070–1600  BC ) (ii) adopted as a surname by the Hu Di Gan (扈地干) family from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD )."]},{"name":"Hooe","meanings":["English: variant of   Hoo   1."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Hoo was born about 1435, in Southwold, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Thomas de Hoo. She married Geoffrey Barrett in 1455, in Blythburgh, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died about 1488, in her hometown, at the age of 55."},"et":{"Abt 1435–Abt 1488":"umbes 1435–umbes 1488","1435–1488":"1435–1488","1431–1487":"1431–1487","1461–1513":"1461–1513","1416–1486":"1416–1486","1513":"1513","1435":"1435","1455":"1455","1488":"1488","1487":"1487","1486":"1486","1431":"1431","Abt 1435":"umbes 1435","1461":"1461","Abt 1488":"umbes 1488","18 July 1487":"18. juuli 1487","1416":"1416","Blythburgh Manor,Southwold,Suffolkshire,England":"Southwold, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Blythburgh, Suffolk, England":"Blythburgh, Suffolk, England","Southwold, Suffolk, England":"Southwold, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1435–Abt 1488":"noin 1435–noin 1488","1435–1488":"1435–1488","1431–1487":"1431–1487","1461–1513":"1461–1513","1416–1486":"1416–1486","1513":"1513","1435":"1435","1455":"1455","1488":"1488","1487":"1487","1486":"1486","1431":"1431","Abt 1435":"noin 